      "content": "it's easy to just say the \"official explanation\" is the real one, but that's exactly how cover-ups work. they provide a plausible technical reason so nobody asks questions. if we look at the missions where the telemetry was supposedly \"degraded\" or the tapes were \"lost,\" like the Apollo 11 raw data tapes that went missing, doesn't that seem way too convenient? it's a pattern. even if you can't find direct proof of a structure, can we at least look at the specific dates and missions where the data loss was most significant? i want to see if there's a correlation between the \"technical failures\" and the most critical moments of the landings.",
      "source": "evaluator"
